# Next.js API routes (BFF)

Read `docs/architecture.md` (Request lifecycle, Authentication) before non-trivial changes.

## Routes

| Route | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `POST /api/session` | Proxy → agent API `POST /api/v1/sessions`; returns `session_id` |
| `POST /api/chat` | Proxy → agent API `POST /api/v1/chat/stream` (SSE); re-emits deltas as AI SDK UI message stream |
| `POST /api/livekit/token` | Mint LiveKit JWT + `RoomAgentDispatch` (server-only secrets) |

Shared client: `src/lib/agent-client.ts` (`AGENT_API_BASE_URL`, optional `WEB_API_KEY` header).

## Chat route pattern

- Input: AI SDK transport body with `sessionId` / `session_id` and `messages[]`
- Extract last user text part; reject if missing
- Call `streamAgentChat(sessionId, userText)` — async generator consuming the backend SSE stream
- Forward each delta as `text-delta` inside `createUIMessageStream` (mapping to AI SDK protocol lives here, not in the agent)

## Session route pattern

- Accept optional `{ session_id }` for resume
- Forward to `createAgentSession()`
- Return JSON with `Cache-Control: no-store`

## LiveKit token route

- Parse `TokenSourceRequest` from LiveKit client
- Resolve chat `sessionId` from `participantMetadata` first, then room name parser
- Set `RoomConfiguration.metadata` to `{"session_id": sessionId}`
- Attach `RoomAgentDispatch` with `LIVEKIT_AGENT_NAME`
- Never log or return API secrets

## Do not

- Expose `WEB_API_KEY`, LiveKit secrets, or Bedrock credentials to the browser
- Call Google Calendar or LangGraph from Route Handlers
- Change AI SDK stream shape without updating `chat-panel.tsx` transport expectations

For LiveKit room naming and voice reconnect semantics, see rule `livekit-voice`.
